Date: 1994-06-13

Title: Hard Thermal Loops in a Moving Plasma and a Magnetic Mass Term

Authors: V.P.Nair

Comments: 10 pages, CCNY-HEP 4/94 (plain TeX)

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B352 (1995) 117-121

We consider the hard thermal loops of QCD for a moving quark-gluon plasma.Generalizing from this we suggest a candidate for the magnetic mass term. Thisterm may also be useful in understanding the mass gap of three-dimensionalnon-Abelian gauge theories.